ctNatPublicIfIndex.name: ctNatPublicIfIndex
ctNatPublicIfIndex.description: This is the value of the MIB II ifindex which identifies the router port connected to the public network.

ctNatPublicIP.name: ctNatPublicIP
ctNatPublicIP.description: This is the IP address of the interface which is selected by ctNatPublicIfIndex.

ctNatPublicMask.name: ctNatPublicMask
ctNatPublicMask.description: This is the subnet mask of the interface which is selected by ctNatPublicIfIndex.

ctNatMaxConn.name: ctNatMaxConn
ctNatMaxConn.description: This is the value of the maximum number of simultaneous connections allowed, using the Network Address Translator application. The default value is 200. Acceptable values are from 40 to 1000.

ctNatTcpTimeout.name: ctNatTcpTimeout
ctNatTcpTimeout.description: This is the value in seconds after which an idle TCP connection will be deleted. The default value is 300. Acceptable values are from 60 to 3600.

ctNatUdpTimeout.name: ctNatUdpTimeout
ctNatUdpTimeout.description: This is the value in seconds after which an idle UDP connection will be deleted. The default value is 120. Acceptable values are from 60 to 3600.

ctNatPktsL2I.name: ctNatPktsL2I
ctNatPktsL2I.description: This is the number of packets which have been forwarded from the private network to the public network since the last reset.

ctNatPktsI2L.name: ctNatPktsI2L
ctNatPktsI2L.description: This is the number of packets which have been forwarded from the public network to the private network since the last reset.

ctNatBytesL2I.name: ctNatBytesL2I
ctNatBytesL2I.description: This is the number of bytes which have been forwarded from the private network to the public network since the last reset.

ctNatBytesI2L.name: ctNatBytesI2L
ctNatBytesI2L.description: This is the number of bytes which have been forwarded from the public network to the private network since the last reset.

ctNatTcpConn.name: ctNatTcpConn
ctNatTcpConn.description: This is the number of active TCP connections using the Network Address Translator application.

ctNatUdpConn.name: ctNatUdpConn
ctNatUdpConn.description: This is the number of active UDP connections using the Network Address Translator application.

ctNatIcmpConn.name: ctNatIcmpConn
ctNatIcmpConn.description: This is the number of active ICMP connections using the Network Address Translator application.

ctNatRetries.name: ctNatRetries
ctNatRetries.description: This is the number of detected TCP retries in both directions since the last reset.

ctNatBadSums.name: ctNatBadSums
ctNatBadSums.description: This is the number of detected checksum errors in both directions since the last reset.

ctNatTotalPkts.name: ctNatTotalPkts
ctNatTotalPkts.description: This is the total number of packets by the application since the last reset.

ctNatBadPkts.name: ctNatBadPkts
ctNatBadPkts.description: This is the total number of packets detected with an invalid format since the last reset.

ctNatResPkts.name: ctNatResPkts
ctNatResPkts.description: This is the total number of packets detected with a reserved address since the last reset.

ctNatTotTcpConn.name: ctNatTotTcpConn
ctNatTotTcpConn.description: This is the number of TCP connections made using the Network Address Translator application since the last reset.

ctNatTotUdpConn.name: ctNatTotUdpConn
ctNatTotUdpConn.description: This is the number of UDP connections made using the Network Address Translator application since the last reset.

ctNatTotIcmpConn.name: ctNatTotIcmpConn
ctNatTotIcmpConn.description: This is the number of ICMP connections made using the Network Address Translator application since the last reset.

ctNatConfigTable.name: ctNatConfigTable
ctNatConfigTable.description: Information describing the configuration parameters for each instance of NAT.

ctNatConfigEntry.name: ctNatConfigEntry
ctNatConfigEntry.description: A description of a single server entry.

ctNatConfigId.name: ctNatConfigId
ctNatConfigId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of groups which belong to the NAT configuration table.

ctNatAdminStatus.name: ctNatAdminStatus
ctNatAdminStatus.description: Used to enable and disable the Network Address Translator method for this instance. This object must be set to enabled for the translation to occur on ctNatLocalIfIndex.

ctNatOperStatus.name: ctNatOperStatus
ctNatOperStatus.description: Indicates the current operating status of the Network Address Translator feature.

ctNatLocalIfIndex.name: ctNatLocalIfIndex
ctNatLocalIfIndex.description: This is the value of the MIB II ifindex which identifies the router port connected to the private network.

ctNatLocalIP.name: ctNatLocalIP
ctNatLocalIP.description: This is the IP address of the interface which serves as the gateway for the private network. With ctNatLocalMask, it serves to define the subnet of the hosts on the network. The preferred address is 192.168.254.254, part of the class C net reserved by RFC1597.

ctNatLocalMask.name: ctNatLocalMask
ctNatLocalMask.description: This is the subnet mask of the interface which serves as the gateway for the private network. With ctNatLocalIP, it serves to define the subnet of the hosts on the network. The preferred mask is 255.255.255.0, part of the class C net reserved by RFC1597.

ctNatTotServerEntries.name: ctNatTotServerEntries
ctNatTotServerEntries.description: This is the total number of server assignments.

ctNatServerListTable.name: ctNatServerListTable
ctNatServerListTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters which designate a local device as a server.

ctNatServerListEntry.name: ctNatServerListEntry
ctNatServerListEntry.description: A description of a single server entry.

ctNatServerId.name: ctNatServerId
ctNatServerId.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of groups which belong to the NAT Server List. This value ranges from 1 to 16.

ctNatProxyServer.name: ctNatProxyServer
ctNatProxyServer.description: A description of a proxy server assignment. The format is private IP address of the server, followed by the public port number, followed by the private port number, followed by the protocol to be handled by the server. The fields are delimited by commas. Each record must be 31 chars or less. Protocol choices are TCP and UDP.

ctNatTotActiveConn.name: ctNatTotActiveConn
ctNatTotActiveConn.description: This is the total number of active connections.

ctNatConnStatsTable.name: ctNatConnStatsTable
ctNatConnStatsTable.description: Information describing the configured parameters which designate a local device as a server.

ctNatConnStatsEntry.name: ctNatConnStatsEntry
ctNatConnStatsEntry.description: A description of a single server entry.

ctNatConnStatsID.name: ctNatConnStatsID
ctNatConnStatsID.description: A unique value identifying an element in a sequence of active connections which belong to the NAT Connection Statistics Group.

ctNatConnStatsForeignIP.name: ctNatConnStatsForeignIP
ctNatConnStatsForeignIP.description: This is the IP address of the foreign host during this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsLocalIP.name: ctNatConnStatsLocalIP
ctNatConnStatsLocalIP.description: This is the IP address of the local host during this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsPublicPort.name: ctNatConnStatsPublicPort
ctNatConnStatsPublicPort.description: This is the port number addressed by an external device. It is also substituted for the local port by NAT on outbound packets.

ctNatConnStatsLocalPort.name: ctNatConnStatsLocalPort
ctNatConnStatsLocalPort.description: This is the local host's port for TCP or UDP for this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsForeignPort.name: ctNatConnStatsForeignPort
ctNatConnStatsForeignPort.description: This is the source port number used by the foreign host for this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsOutgoingPkts.name: ctNatConnStatsOutgoingPkts
ctNatConnStatsOutgoingPkts.description: This is the number of packets that have been sent from the local net to the public net by this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsOutgoingBytes.name: ctNatConnStatsOutgoingBytes
ctNatConnStatsOutgoingBytes.description: This is the number of bytes that have been sent from the local net to the public net by this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsIncomingPkts.name: ctNatConnStatsIncomingPkts
ctNatConnStatsIncomingPkts.description: This is the number of packets that have been sent from the public net to the local net by this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsIncomingBytes.name: ctNatConnStatsIncomingBytes
ctNatConnStatsIncomingBytes.description: This is the number of bytes that have been sent from the public net to the local net by this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsTimeSinceUse.name: ctNatConnStatsTimeSinceUse
ctNatConnStatsTimeSinceUse.description: This is the time in seconds since the last packet was sent or received on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsProtocol.name: ctNatConnStatsProtocol
ctNatConnStatsProtocol.description: This is the type of IP protocol used by this active connection. Options are 1 = ICMP, 6 = TCP and 17 = UDP.

ctNatConnStatsTCPSeq.name: ctNatConnStatsTCPSeq
ctNatConnStatsTCPSeq.description: This is the last TCP sequence number of local host sent on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsTCPAck.name: ctNatConnStatsTCPAck
ctNatConnStatsTCPAck.description: This is the last TCP acknowledgement number of local host sent on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsTCPState.name: ctNatConnStatsTCPState
ctNatConnStatsTCPState.description: This is the TCP connection state value on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsLocalRetrys.name: ctNatConnStatsLocalRetrys
ctNatConnStatsLocalRetrys.description: This is the number of TCP retries by the local host on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsForeignRetrys.name: ctNatConnStatsForeignRetrys
ctNatConnStatsForeignRetrys.description: This is the number of TCP retries by the foreign host on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsLocalChecksum.name: ctNatConnStatsLocalChecksum
ctNatConnStatsLocalChecksum.description: This is the number of times checksum failed in a packet from the local host on this active connection.

ctNatConnStatsForeignChecksum.name: ctNatConnStatsForeignChecksum
ctNatConnStatsForeignChecksum.description: This is the number of times checksum failed in a packet from the foreign host on this active connection.
